Module it.polimi.ingsw
Package it.polimi.ingsw.model.cards

Class StartCard

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.model.cards.Card
it.polimi.ingsw.model.cards.StartCard
All Implemented Interfaces:
Drawable, Serializable
public class StartCard extends Card
Represents Starting cards. This kind of cards is only used in the very beginning of the game. It's the first card on the Players board and has some peculiarities compared to PlayCards.

  • Constructor Details

    • StartCard

      public StartCard(String cardID, String frontPath, String backPath, Corner frontTopLeft, Corner frontTopRight, Corner frontBottomLeft, Corner frontBottomRight, Corner backTopLeft, Corner backTopRight, Corner backBottomLeft, Corner backBottomRight, ItemCollection permanentResources)
      Constructs a StartCard object with specified parameters. StartCards also has different corners on the back side, that's why the constructor needs two sets of corners.
      Parameters:
      cardID - the card's identifier
      frontPath - path to the image that represents the front side of the card
      backPath - path to the image that represents the back side of the card
      frontTopLeft - the top-left corner on the front side of the card.
      frontTopRight - the top-right corner on the front side of the card.
      frontBottomLeft - the bottom-left corner on the front side of the card.
      frontBottomRight - the bottom-right corner on the front side of the card.
      backTopLeft - the top-left corner on the back side of the card.
      backTopRight - the top-right corner on the back side of the card.
      backBottomLeft - the bottom-left corner on the back side of the card.
      backBottomRight - the bottom-right corner on the back side of the card.
      permanentResources - ItemCollection representing the set of permanent resources on the back of the card.
